to the editor re kabuki radio 'creeping meatballism and other peculiar riffs on america week in review march 26 not only did the stories of the radio personality jean shepherd always have complete endings but they were also often nested one inside the other with another starting before the previous one finished that meant that at the end of mr shepherd 's air time you would hear the end of each story in the reverse order that it started i was an avid listener i never heard him miss it was so neatly done peter hay summit nj march 26 2000

